{{refimprove|date=September 2018}}
'''Aspidomancy''' (from the Greek word "aspis" meaning shield)<ref>{{cite web |title=Aspidomancy |url=http://www.yourdictionary.com/aspidomancy |website=YourDictionary |accessdate=23 September 2018}}</ref> is a form of [[divination]] based on the interpretation of patterns on a [[shield]].  Reading the patterns is believed to give some insight into the future.  Readers study the shield, looking for a pattern that may represent symbols or pictures.  They interpret these symbols and pictures as clues as to what is going to happen in the future.

Aspidomancy can also refer to the method of divination of sitting on a shield and reciting [[incantation]]s to summon an entity or enter a [[trance]], in order to gain knowledge. This method was first described in the 17th century by French writer [[Pierre de Lancre]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Aspidomancy |url=https://www.themystica.com/aspidomancy/ |website=The Mystica |accessdate=23 September 2018}}</ref>

