{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2017}} {{Use Indian English|date=August 2017}} {{Infobox Cave | name = Khed Caves | photo =Khed caves.jpg | photo_caption =Khed caves | location = | depth = | length = | map = India#India Maharashtra |relief=yes | map_width = | map_caption = | label = Khed Caves | map_alt = | coords = {{coord|17.721544|73.398402|display=inline, title}} | survey = | survey_format = | discovery = | geology = | entrance_count = | entrance_list = | difficulty = | hazards = | access = | translation = | language = | pronunciation = }} '''Khed Caves''', also '''Bouddh Caves''', are a series of ancient Buddhist caves in the city of [[Khed, Ratnagiri|Khed]], [[Maharashtra]], [[India]].<ref name=AD/><ref>{{cite book |last1=Nairne |first1=Alexander Kyd |title=History of the Konkan |date=1988 |publisher=Asian Educational Services |isbn=9788120602755 |page=9 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=nzPCcILP-XwC&pg=PA9 |language=en}}</ref>
The group of caves comprises a large [[vihara]], with three cells for monks, and with a [[stupa]] in the back located in an oblong room.<ref name=AD>{{cite book |last1=Deshpande |first1=Aruna |title=Buddhist India Rediscovered |date=2013 |publisher=Jaico Publishing House |isbn=9788184952476 |page=222 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=nbUQAgAAQBAJ&pg=PT222 |language=en}}</ref> There are also four smaller caves in the group.<ref name=AD/> The caves are in a rather derelict state.
