'''{{lang|nci|Tiānquiztli}}''' ({{IPA-nah|tiaːŋˈkistɬi}}; [[Classical Nahuatl]] for "marketplace") was the [[Aztec]]'s name for the [[Pleiades]].  Time was measured by movements of the stars and the sun. Their calendar was based upon a 52 year cycle. They watched {{lang|nci|Tiānquitzli}} (Pleiades) closely.

