[[File:Vadakku vasal.jpg|right|thumb|The Structure erected above the Vatakku Vasal where [[Ayya Vaikundar]] performed the [[Tavam]]]]
'''Vatakku Vasal''' (which means "north entrance") is the north entrance of [[Swamithoppe]] [[pathi]]. It was here [[Ayya Vaikundar]] performed his Tavam. This is considered sacred by the followers of [[Ayyavazhi]]. During the Eleven-day festival in Swamithoppe, on the eight day after the [[Kali vettai]], scene of austirity ([[Ekanai]]) of Ayya Vaikundar was performed.

